==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fetlock
<hw>Fet"lock</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>fetlak</ets>, <ets>fitlock</ets>, cf. Icel. <ets>fet</ets> pace,
step, <ets>fit</ets> webbed foot of water birds, akin to E.
<ets>foot</ets>. ⟦root⟧ 77. See <er>Foot</er>.]</ety> <def>The
cushionlike projection, bearing a tuft of long hair, on the back side of
the leg above the hoof of the horse and similar animals. Also, the joint
of the limb at this point (between the great pastern bone and the
metacarpus), or the tuft of hair.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their wounded steeds⟦br⟧
Fret <qex>fetlock</qex> deep in gore.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fetor</ent>⟦br⟧
